		<title>03EMPLOYMENT IN SUCKLEY</title>
		<content>{                                      
                                       
                                       
                                       
      The largest employer is the{Bruff
{Manufacturing Company,}with fifty     
 local people (mostly men) on the shop 
 floor.  On average the{farms}employ   
 one or two people, the most being     
 seven.  Women are able to get{domestic
{work}and a little{seasonal horticult- 
{ural employment. }Firms in Malvern and
 Worcester 'bus their employees daily. 
 Professional people tend to commute by
 private car to places as far apart as 
 Hereford, Ledbury and Birmingham.     
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
